 that can be accreted into galaxy halos, which may explain why the\nbaryon fraction in a spiral galaxy is in general much lower than the universal\nbaryon fraction, f_B~0.16, in the standard Lambda CDM model.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Nov 2003 20:44:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 19 Nov 2003 21:06:50 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 21 Nov 2003 23:55:50 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 10 Jun 2004 14:06:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-30"}
